1
00:01:51,445 --> 00:01:53,356
MICHAEL: <i>My dear children.</i>

2
00:01:53,989 --> 00:01:58,449
<i>It is now better than several
years since I moved to New York</i>

3
00:01:59,202 --> 00:02:02,490
<i>and I haven't seen you
as much as I would like to.</i>

4
00:02:03,624 --> 00:02:07,618
<i>I hope you will come to this
ceremony of Papal honors,</i>

5
00:02:07,711 --> 00:02:10,123
<i>given for my charitable work.</i>

6
00:02:12,382 --> 00:02:15,500
<i>The only wealth in
this world is children.</i>

7
00:02:15,594 --> 00:02:18,507
<i>More than all the money
and power on earth,</i>

8
00:02:19,765 --> 00:02:22,097
<i>you are my treasure.</i>

9
00:02:23,644 --> 00:02:25,931
<i>Anthony and Mary,</i>

10
00:02:26,063 --> 00:02:30,978
<i>although I entrusted your education to
your mother for your own best interest,</i>

11
00:02:31,068 --> 00:02:36,154
<i>I look forward to seeing you, and to
a new period of harmony in our lives.</i>

12
00:02:38,283 --> 00:02:42,823
<i>Perhaps you might prevail upon
your mother to come to this celebration,</i>

13
00:02:43,455 --> 00:02:48,200
<i>and that from time to time, we can
all see each other at family functions.</i>

14
00:02:49,670 --> 00:02:54,005
<i>Anyway, I remain your loving father.</i>

15
00:02:55,967 --> 00:02:58,379
[ARCHBISHOP CHANTING IN LATIN]

16
00:03:03,767 --> 00:03:07,635
[ALL RESPONDING IN LATIN]

17
00:03:20,450 --> 00:03:22,817
[PRIEST SPEAKING LATIN]

18
00:03:23,870 --> 00:03:26,532
Hail Mary, full of grace…

19
00:03:27,124 --> 00:03:29,991
[ARCHBISHOP SPEAKING LATIN]

20
00:03:30,085 --> 00:03:32,668
…blessed art Thou amongst women,

21
00:03:33,422 --> 00:03:36,585
and blessed is the fruit
of Thy womb, Jesus.

22
00:03:37,843 --> 00:03:42,212
Holy Mary, mother of
God, pray for us sinners…

23
00:03:42,472 --> 00:03:45,055
[PRIEST SPEAKING LATIN]

24
00:03:47,102 --> 00:03:48,433
[GUNSHOT]

25
00:04:07,205 --> 00:04:13,247
ARCHBISHOP: Almighty God, bless the
insignia of Saint Sebastian the martyr,

26
00:04:13,378 --> 00:04:19,169
that it may contribute to the
sacredness of him to whom it is given.

27
00:04:31,772 --> 00:04:35,310
ARCHBISHOP: Do you,
Michael, promise to be faithful

28
00:04:35,400 --> 00:04:37,983
to the noble purposes of this Order,

29
00:04:38,695 --> 00:04:43,610
to have a special care for the poor,
the needy and those who are ill?

30
00:04:43,700 --> 00:04:45,566
MICHAEL: I do so promise.

31
00:04:45,660 --> 00:04:47,526
[ARCHBISHOP BLESSING IN LATIN]

32
00:05:01,009 --> 00:05:03,967
May the blessing of Almighty God,

33
00:05:04,054 --> 00:05:09,140
Father, Son and Holy Spirit

34
00:05:09,226 --> 00:05:14,221
descend upon you and
remain with you forever.

35
00:05:17,275 --> 00:05:18,982
[CHOIR SINGING]

36
00:05:24,616 --> 00:05:26,072
[INDISTINCT]

37
00:06:01,653 --> 00:06:04,270
[TRADITIONAL ITALIAN MUSIC PLAYING]

38
00:06:05,073 --> 00:06:06,734
[SINGING "EH CUMPARI"]

39
00:06:38,064 --> 00:06:40,726
[INDISTINCT CHATTERING]

40
00:06:48,283 --> 00:06:50,991
Vincent, our name is not on the list.

41
00:06:53,580 --> 00:06:57,619
Write it in. Mancini. M-A-N-C-I-N-I.

42
00:06:59,336 --> 00:07:01,668
-Problem?
-My name isn't on the list.

43
00:07:01,796 --> 00:07:06,586
-Then you have to leave immediately.
-You want to dance with me?

44
00:07:06,676 --> 00:07:09,839
Joe, it's Vinnie. These are our guests.

45
00:07:09,971 --> 00:07:12,008
I'm sorry. I'm sorry, sir.

46
00:07:12,098 --> 00:07:14,339
Welcome to the party.

47
00:07:16,144 --> 00:07:18,010
[SINGING CONTINUES]

48
00:07:18,188 --> 00:07:20,145
[INDISTINCT]

49
00:07:24,361 --> 00:07:26,022
[SINGING ALONG]

50
00:07:27,364 --> 00:07:28,946
[MUSIC STOPS]

51
00:07:32,285 --> 00:07:34,492
[MIMICKING MELODY]

52
00:07:36,164 --> 00:07:38,872
[A FEW PEOPLE RESUME SINGING]

53
00:07:39,000 --> 00:07:41,207
[HUMMING MELODY IN ENCOURAGEMENT]

54
00:07:43,880 --> 00:07:45,666
[PEOPLE JOINING IN]

55
00:07:49,719 --> 00:07:52,006
[GUESTS APPLAUDING]

56
00:07:55,225 --> 00:07:58,058
[INDISTINCT CHATTERING]

57
00:08:07,404 --> 00:08:11,693
-It's good to see you.
-Good to see you. This is my husband.

58
00:08:11,783 --> 00:08:14,024
-Sit down.
-My son, Anthony.

59
00:08:15,286 --> 00:08:20,452
The Order of Saint Sebastian is one of
the highest honors the Church awards.

60
00:08:20,583 --> 00:08:22,824
It was first granted by Pope…

61
00:08:22,961 --> 00:08:26,295
What about Mr. Corleone's
connections with gambling?

62
00:08:26,798 --> 00:08:28,459
The press kits have…

63
00:08:28,591 --> 00:08:30,843
What about his involvement
with the underworld?

64
00:08:30,927 --> 00:08:32,088
Cut the crap.

65
00:08:33,096 --> 00:08:35,838
The Pope, the Holy Father himself,

66
00:08:35,932 --> 00:08:40,597
has today blessed Michael Corleone.
Do you know better than the Pope?

67
00:08:41,438 --> 00:08:44,601
Vincent! She loves you.

68
00:08:44,733 --> 00:08:46,394
Yeah?

69
00:08:50,447 --> 00:08:52,063
I love you too.

70
00:08:57,954 --> 00:09:00,912
Hi, Vincent. I remember you.

71
00:09:02,667 --> 00:09:06,706
-From where?
-The last party we were at together.

72
00:09:06,796 --> 00:09:09,959
-Did you come to the club?
-No, it was a wedding.

73
00:09:12,427 --> 00:09:14,839
I was eight and you were 15.

74
00:09:16,014 --> 00:09:19,006
I had many girlfriends when I was 15.

75
00:09:19,142 --> 00:09:21,179
-Eight-year-olds?
-Especially them.

76
00:09:23,688 --> 00:09:25,770
Where's Mary?

77
00:09:25,857 --> 00:09:30,818
Would somebody please hail Mary?
Excuse me, Your Excellency.

78
00:09:30,945 --> 00:09:34,859
You haven't kissed me hello yet.
Relatives always kiss.

79
00:09:35,116 --> 00:09:38,154
-[LAUGHING] Now we're related?
-I'm your little cousin.

80
00:09:46,503 --> 00:09:49,541
-Who's your father?
-I'll give you a hint.

81
00:09:50,840 --> 00:09:52,547
He's Italian.

82
00:09:52,675 --> 00:09:55,963
Mary, we've been waiting for you.

83
00:09:56,054 --> 00:10:00,343
Remember to keep your voice low.

84
00:10:00,475 --> 00:10:02,887
And smile. Don't forget to smile.

85
00:10:03,019 --> 00:10:04,885
[GUESTS APPLAUDING]

86
00:10:11,361 --> 00:10:13,352
[PRESENTATION MUSIC PLAYING]

87
00:10:21,204 --> 00:10:23,115
[GREETING GUESTS IN ITALIAN]

88
00:10:23,206 --> 00:10:27,450
The honorary chairman of
the Vito Corleone Foundation,

89
00:10:27,544 --> 00:10:29,751
my daughter, Mary Corleone.

90
00:10:39,681 --> 00:10:41,012
Thanks.

91
00:10:42,559 --> 00:10:47,269
I think I inherited my father's love
for speechmaking. Here it goes.

92
00:10:49,023 --> 00:10:53,608
The Vito Corleone Foundation
helps the poor in every country,

93
00:10:53,736 --> 00:10:57,775
gives grants to artists,
funds medical research,

94
00:10:57,907 --> 00:11:02,697
and is particularly dedicated
to the resurrection of Sicily.

95
00:11:03,413 --> 00:11:05,495
Archbishop Gilday,

96
00:11:05,623 --> 00:11:10,709
here is 100 million dollars for the poor
of Sicily, in the name of Vito Corleone.

97
00:11:10,795 --> 00:11:12,502
[GUESTS MURMURING]

98
00:11:12,589 --> 00:11:14,956
Don't spend it all in one place.

99
00:11:32,942 --> 00:11:38,108
Mary, I'm so proud of you.

100
00:11:39,824 --> 00:11:41,690
[CONNIE CHATTERING]

101
00:11:45,163 --> 00:11:46,870
Michael…

102
00:11:46,956 --> 00:11:49,789
You've done a wonderful thing for Sicily.

103
00:11:50,668 --> 00:11:54,332
Let's hope that the money
gets to the people who need it.

104
00:11:54,464 --> 00:11:55,670
Amen.

105
00:11:55,798 --> 00:12:00,884
CONNIE: …the most
important part: Johnny Fontane!

106
00:12:09,687 --> 00:12:12,679
Thank you very much.
I'm happy to be here.

107
00:12:12,815 --> 00:12:18,401
I would like you to join me in honoring
Commendatore Michael Corleone.

108
00:12:22,700 --> 00:12:26,034
I have something
special for our godfather.

109
00:12:26,162 --> 00:12:30,702
I happen to know his favorite song.
Michael, where are you going?

110
00:12:30,833 --> 00:12:34,451
I'm off to the kitchen to hear
some Tony Bennett records.

111
00:12:34,545 --> 00:12:35,660
[PEOPLE LAUGHING]

112
00:12:35,755 --> 00:12:38,292
Your favorite song, "Salsiccia's Own."

113
00:12:38,383 --> 00:12:41,466
I'm having a salsiccia sandwich.
I'll be back.

114
00:12:41,552 --> 00:12:43,668
[SINGING "TO EACH HIS OWN"]

115
00:13:16,045 --> 00:13:17,456
Hello, Kay.

116
00:13:27,890 --> 00:13:30,757
Congratulations, Michael.
That's quite an honor.

117
00:13:30,893 --> 00:13:33,885
But a little expensive, wouldn't you say?

118
00:13:36,733 --> 00:13:39,725
-Cake?
-No, thank you.

119
00:13:44,574 --> 00:13:46,235
[SINGING IN ITALIAN]

120
00:13:53,624 --> 00:13:56,912
-It's been a long time, hasn't it?
-Yeah.

121
00:13:57,003 --> 00:13:58,914
-Eight years.
-Yeah.

122
00:13:59,756 --> 00:14:01,588
You look wonderful.

123
00:14:05,178 --> 00:14:09,797
Your son has something he wants to
talk to you about. I came here for him.

124
00:14:36,793 --> 00:14:37,783
[DOOR OPENS]

125
00:14:44,634 --> 00:14:50,004
-What's wrong with being a lawyer?
-He wants his life to be in music.

126
00:14:51,891 --> 00:14:56,226
Music is great, I love music.
But he should finish what he started.

127
00:14:56,312 --> 00:14:57,677
Anthony…

128
00:14:58,314 --> 00:15:00,726
-I'm going my own way.
-Your own way?

129
00:15:01,734 --> 00:15:03,566
-Professional singer?
-Yes.

130
00:15:03,653 --> 00:15:06,816
What happens if you fail?

131
00:15:06,906 --> 00:15:10,069
-I won't fail.
-Men always believe that.

132
00:15:10,159 --> 00:15:14,369
A law degree is like
taking out insurance.

133
00:15:15,206 --> 00:15:19,074
-After that you can work for me…
-I will never work for you.

134
00:15:20,378 --> 00:15:22,210
I have bad memories.

135
00:15:24,006 --> 00:15:26,498
Every family has bad memories.

136
00:15:30,221 --> 00:15:34,761
I'll always be your son, but won't
have anything to do with your business.

137
00:15:37,353 --> 00:15:40,766
Anthony… finish the law degree.

138
00:15:42,358 --> 00:15:43,519
No.

139
00:16:01,043 --> 00:16:04,877
Well, that he got from you. That "no."

140
00:16:07,925 --> 00:16:13,045
-You could've helped me convince him.
-Convince him of what?

141
00:16:13,723 --> 00:16:14,963
Of what?

142
00:16:15,808 --> 00:16:17,298
He throws his life away.

143
00:16:17,393 --> 00:16:18,599
[KAY SNORTS]

144
00:16:18,728 --> 00:16:20,560
He throws greatness away.

145
00:16:21,564 --> 00:16:23,271
This is greatness?

146
00:16:24,775 --> 00:16:29,269
Now that you're so respectable,
you're more dangerous than ever.

147
00:16:29,405 --> 00:16:33,444
I preferred you when you
were just a common Mafia hood.

148
00:16:34,619 --> 00:16:35,905
Okay.

149
00:16:37,163 --> 00:16:40,576
-Can we talk common sense here?
-All right.

150
00:16:47,298 --> 00:16:49,790
Tony knows that you killed Fredo.

151
00:16:56,516 --> 00:16:59,884
-What did you come here for?
-To protect my son.

152
00:17:00,019 --> 00:17:04,934
Not to see you disguised by your church.
That was a shameful ceremony.

153
00:17:09,654 --> 00:17:12,146
I spent my life protecting my son.

154
00:17:12,782 --> 00:17:16,275
I spent my life protecting my family!

155
00:17:16,369 --> 00:17:18,451
Let's be reasonable, okay?

156
00:17:19,664 --> 00:17:24,033
That's your big thing, isn't it, Michael?
Reason,

157
00:17:25,127 --> 00:17:28,540
-backed up by murder.
-[WHISPERING] Oh, God.

158
00:17:30,341 --> 00:17:33,800
-You hate me. You hate me.
-No.

159
00:17:33,886 --> 00:17:35,672
I don't hate you.

160
00:17:37,515 --> 00:17:39,131
I dread you.

161
00:17:43,020 --> 00:17:49,187
I did what I could, Kay, to protect all
of you from the horrors of this world.

162
00:17:50,570 --> 00:17:52,732
But you became my horror.

163
00:18:02,498 --> 00:18:05,911
The children still love you, though.
Especially Mary.

164
00:18:09,046 --> 00:18:10,753
That's something.

165
00:18:13,175 --> 00:18:16,668
We can build on that. For their sake…

166
00:18:20,683 --> 00:18:22,048
let's try.

167
00:18:22,685 --> 00:18:28,055
Only if you let Tony go free to
have his own life, away from you.

168
00:18:35,406 --> 00:18:37,113
I'll let Tony go.

169
00:18:39,702 --> 00:18:41,192
Thank you.

170
00:18:54,884 --> 00:18:57,046
[DISCO MUSIC PLAYING]

171
00:19:04,143 --> 00:19:06,100
[INDISTINCT CHATTERING]

172
00:19:06,812 --> 00:19:08,723
[PLAYING JEW'S HARP]

173
00:19:15,946 --> 00:19:17,937
-Hi.
-Hi.

174
00:19:19,950 --> 00:19:25,241
You could hurt somebody with those.
Let me show you around.

175
00:19:25,331 --> 00:19:27,698
Can you get me an
interview with Corleone?

176
00:19:27,792 --> 00:19:32,002
No. I'm a relative, but I can't do that.
What else can I do for you?

177
00:19:33,506 --> 00:19:36,419
-Handsome, but useless.
-Oh, yeah?

178
00:19:36,509 --> 00:19:39,342
-That's okay, I'll gamble.
-Do you like to gamble?

179
00:19:39,428 --> 00:19:43,296
Let's go to Atlantic City.
I'll show you how to gamble.

180
00:19:43,432 --> 00:19:48,142
-How do I know what numbers to bet?
-Do I look like a guy who's gonna lose?

181
00:19:48,270 --> 00:19:49,476
Well…

182
00:19:52,149 --> 00:19:54,140
Spooky-looking guy there.

183
00:19:54,276 --> 00:19:59,771
-What's a guy like that doing here?
-That's Joey Zasa's bulldog.

184
00:19:59,865 --> 00:20:01,947
-You know him?
-Yeah, I do.

185
00:20:02,868 --> 00:20:07,283
His name is Anthony Squigilaro.
They call him "The Ant."

186
00:20:07,998 --> 00:20:10,456
He dips his bullets in cyanide.

187
00:20:12,002 --> 00:20:13,788
[KNOCK ON DOOR]

188
00:20:19,301 --> 00:20:20,883
Don Altobello.

189
00:20:22,388 --> 00:20:25,801
-I've come to pay my respects.
<i>-Grazie.</i>

190
00:20:29,353 --> 00:20:31,811
You honor my father's friendship.

191
00:20:31,897 --> 00:20:33,979
Where is my goddaughter?

192
00:20:35,860 --> 00:20:38,022
-Constanza!
-Don Altobello.

193
00:20:38,571 --> 00:20:43,065
It was not so long ago that I
held you in these old hands.

194
00:20:47,163 --> 00:20:48,824
[SPEAKING ITALIAN]

195
00:20:51,584 --> 00:20:56,750
Michael, I've lost all the
venom, all the juice of youth.

196
00:20:56,839 --> 00:21:02,005
I've lost the lust for women,
and now my mind is clear.

197
00:21:02,678 --> 00:21:09,095
My duty to God is clear.
I have a special favor to ask of you.

198
00:21:10,686 --> 00:21:17,558
Can I attach my name to
the Vito Corleone Foundation,

199
00:21:18,194 --> 00:21:23,280
so that you and I can be
joined in name and spirit?

200
00:21:25,868 --> 00:21:27,654
One million dollars.

201
00:21:27,745 --> 00:21:28,860
[CONNIE EXCLAIMING]

202
00:21:28,954 --> 00:21:31,946
A lot of money…

203
00:21:33,542 --> 00:21:37,456
-Godfather.
-Don Altobello, you have such a heart.

204
00:21:40,424 --> 00:21:44,759
Come, let's go and sample
some of that old <i>vino.</i>

205
00:21:51,602 --> 00:21:55,061
The Vatican knows nothing
about these shareholders.

206
00:21:55,147 --> 00:21:56,353
Good.

207
00:21:56,440 --> 00:22:01,276
I have a tendency to worry. We've
increased our position substantially.

208
00:22:01,403 --> 00:22:05,943
-Naturally, I worry.
-Stop worrying, we have an agreement.

209
00:22:06,951 --> 00:22:09,909
Good.
How do you think I got this gray hair?

210
00:22:09,995 --> 00:22:15,741
Two seconds… Thank you for your
contribution to the swimming-pool.

211
00:22:15,835 --> 00:22:20,045
We need your help on Sam
Wallace's candidacy for judgeship.

212
00:22:20,130 --> 00:22:22,747
-We can always use a good judge.
-Thanks.

213
00:22:22,842 --> 00:22:24,458
Andrew!

214
00:22:24,593 --> 00:22:28,461
My godson Andrew Hagen.
My brother Tom's eldest boy.

215
00:22:28,597 --> 00:22:33,091
He's been assistant to
Bishop Breelan for three years.

216
00:22:33,185 --> 00:22:37,474
-Hopes to be assigned to the Vatican.
-Rome needs fine young priests.

217
00:22:37,606 --> 00:22:40,598
His mother Teresa Hagen, Bishop Gilday.

218
00:22:41,610 --> 00:22:43,100
Honored to meet you.

219
00:22:43,195 --> 00:22:46,153
Mr. Corleone. Hi. Grace Hamilton.

220
00:22:47,491 --> 00:22:51,985
Vincent Mancini promised to tell you
about me. That maybe you'd see me.

221
00:22:52,329 --> 00:22:55,447
-Did Vincent Mancini call about her?
-NERI: No.

222
00:22:55,541 --> 00:22:59,830
-You promised to stay out there, twice.
-I know.

223
00:23:01,005 --> 00:23:04,999
Joey Zasa showed up.
He's waiting in the lobby.

224
00:23:05,134 --> 00:23:09,469
<i>He wants to personally congratulate you.
Show his respect.</i>

225
00:23:09,555 --> 00:23:14,516
-Do I have to see him?
-He says you're his <i>patron.</i>

226
00:23:17,688 --> 00:23:19,850
Hey, Vinnie!

227
00:23:20,816 --> 00:23:23,478
-Who's your favorite aunt?
-You are.

228
00:23:26,196 --> 00:23:29,689
Today I'll talk to Michael
about your little problem.

229
00:23:30,492 --> 00:23:33,701
If you'd warned me, I would
have worn a better suit.

230
00:23:35,247 --> 00:23:38,114
The Meucci Association has elected you

231
00:23:38,208 --> 00:23:40,825
Italian-American Man of the Year.

232
00:23:42,713 --> 00:23:44,078
Meucci…

233
00:23:47,092 --> 00:23:48,582
Who's Meucci?

234
00:23:49,845 --> 00:23:55,841
The Italian-American who invented
the telephone, one year before Bell.

235
00:23:59,688 --> 00:24:02,680
And this is the reason you've come today?

236
00:24:05,194 --> 00:24:06,776
[SPEAKING ITALIAN]

237
00:24:09,949 --> 00:24:11,064
I…

238
00:24:14,370 --> 00:24:16,737
I've got a stone in my shoe.

239
00:24:18,207 --> 00:24:20,574
A two-bit punk who works for me.

240
00:24:21,460 --> 00:24:24,794
The one who thinks he's related to you.

241
