477
00:44:58,613 --> 00:45:01,025
Let me have this microphone here.

478
00:45:01,157 --> 00:45:06,869
Will we let a criminal run our company?
He's got the map of Sicily on his face!

479
00:45:06,954 --> 00:45:08,194
CHAIRMAN: Order!

480
00:45:08,289 --> 00:45:10,997
He's either a Catholic or a mafioso…

481
00:45:11,125 --> 00:45:12,115
[FEEDBACK ECHOING]

482
00:45:12,251 --> 00:45:13,502
[MAN CONTINUES CLAMORING
WITHOUT AMPLIFICATION]

483
00:45:13,586 --> 00:45:17,329
The Hamilton Investors Group
cannot support this proposal.

484
00:45:18,758 --> 00:45:20,590
Your Excellency…

485
00:45:21,469 --> 00:45:23,085
Mr. Chairman

486
00:45:23,596 --> 00:45:29,308
the Vatican Bank feels that
International Immobiliare…

487
00:45:31,604 --> 00:45:35,313
Will be safe in Mr. Corleone's hands.

488
00:45:36,108 --> 00:45:41,023
…subject to audit and final ratification,
which must take place in Rome.

489
00:45:41,155 --> 00:45:44,489
Please join me in welcoming
Mr. Michael Corleone.

490
00:45:55,294 --> 00:45:56,500
Dad?

491
00:45:59,340 --> 00:46:02,332
Tony says that I'm a
front for the foundation.

492
00:46:04,345 --> 00:46:07,212
That you're using me to pull the strings.

493
00:46:07,974 --> 00:46:10,966
-To get the money where you want it.
-Please!

494
00:46:11,477 --> 00:46:14,469
-To shine up your public image.
-Mary!

495
00:46:15,564 --> 00:46:19,057
Mary, this is real.
This foundation is real.

496
00:46:22,029 --> 00:46:27,024
I wanted Anthony to be part of it.
I thought you would be together on this.

497
00:46:27,159 --> 00:46:31,574
I won't interfere.
I'll help, but only if you ask.

498
00:46:31,706 --> 00:46:33,663
What is this really for?

499
00:46:34,542 --> 00:46:37,705
Why are you doing this?
Why am I doing this?

500
00:46:39,547 --> 00:46:44,166
I'm doing this for my children.
You're doing it for your children too.

501
00:46:45,177 --> 00:46:48,295
This foundation is
supposed to help all people.

502
00:46:48,389 --> 00:46:50,801
That's the purpose.

503
00:46:50,891 --> 00:46:55,431
This is legitimate.
Mary, I swear, this is legitimate.

504
00:46:59,734 --> 00:47:02,692
Dad, I want this to
bring me closer to you.

505
00:47:11,120 --> 00:47:14,863
I would burn in hell to keep you safe.

506
00:47:29,096 --> 00:47:32,134
Go in the other car.
I'll ride with Michael.

507
00:47:32,266 --> 00:47:33,882
Go, go, go.

508
00:47:47,948 --> 00:47:53,409
As your family's oldest friend, I'm
always chosen to bring you messages.

509
00:47:56,248 --> 00:47:58,410
Tell me, Don Altobello.

510
00:48:00,961 --> 00:48:05,751
Your old partners are grateful
for the money you made them.

511
00:48:05,841 --> 00:48:07,627
They worship you,

512
00:48:08,427 --> 00:48:14,469
but their hearts are broken, because
they think you abandoned them.

513
00:48:15,267 --> 00:48:21,559
They want to share your deal on
Immobiliare, to be a family again.

514
00:48:21,649 --> 00:48:24,141
It can purify their money.

515
00:48:26,487 --> 00:48:28,273
This I cannot do.

516
00:48:31,158 --> 00:48:33,991
Immobiliare must be legitimate.

517
00:48:36,455 --> 00:48:37,661
I know.

518
00:48:38,707 --> 00:48:40,789
But they're unhappy.

519
00:48:42,878 --> 00:48:44,209
And you?

520
00:48:45,214 --> 00:48:50,630
I ask nothing for myself.
Only peace in my old age.

521
00:48:51,178 --> 00:48:54,296
But I must please the world around me.

522
00:48:56,392 --> 00:49:02,308
Michael, your father was a reasonable man.
Learn from him.

523
00:49:04,817 --> 00:49:07,980
I learned many things from my father.

524
00:49:13,659 --> 00:49:19,154
Call a meeting, my friend, so
there are no debts or grudges.

525
00:49:20,374 --> 00:49:23,207
We will make the peace, you and I.

526
00:49:32,845 --> 00:49:34,995
[BROADCASTER CHATTERING
IN ITALIAN ON RADIO]

527
00:49:40,352 --> 00:49:43,219
[IN ITALIAN] <i>The Vatican announced today…</i>

528
00:49:43,355 --> 00:49:47,098
<i>That Pope Paul VI has
canceled his Sunday blessing…</i>

529
00:49:47,234 --> 00:49:49,066
<i>Due to ill health.</i>

530
00:49:49,236 --> 00:49:52,228
<i>His physician has ordered total bed rest…</i>

531
00:49:52,448 --> 00:49:55,190
<i>And cessation of all activities.</i>

532
00:50:03,209 --> 00:50:05,200
They've had a press conference.

533
00:50:05,294 --> 00:50:08,457
The Pope's condition is grave.
<i>"Gravissimo."</i>

534
00:50:20,893 --> 00:50:22,930
[ALL PRAYING IN LATIN]

535
00:50:37,326 --> 00:50:40,785
[IN GERMAN] The purpose
of this meeting is to ratify…

536
00:50:41,080 --> 00:50:44,573
The motion passed by our
shareholders in New York.

537
00:50:46,126 --> 00:50:47,412
[IN ENGLISH] Please…

538
00:50:48,379 --> 00:50:52,964
Our group represents a
consortium of Catholic businessmen

539
00:50:53,050 --> 00:50:55,917
against the Corleone control.

540
00:50:56,887 --> 00:51:02,132
The Vatican has cast its vote.
Corleone Group already controls the Board.

541
00:51:02,226 --> 00:51:06,811
According to the Lateran Treaty,
the Vatican vote must be ratified here.

542
00:51:06,939 --> 00:51:09,055
Here in Rome, by the Pope.

543
00:51:13,153 --> 00:51:16,271
The Pope is gravely ill.

544
00:51:17,783 --> 00:51:21,321
Until he recovers, I am powerless.

545
00:51:22,621 --> 00:51:25,613
-What if he dies?
-Then

546
00:51:26,458 --> 00:51:29,917
as you Americans say, all bets are off.

547
00:51:30,004 --> 00:51:31,961
Gentlemen, please.

548
00:51:33,340 --> 00:51:36,674
This is a brief delay. Nothing more.

549
00:51:41,849 --> 00:51:44,136
Your Excellency, gentlemen…

550
00:51:45,352 --> 00:51:50,597
I advise you to join us in our
prayers for the Holy Father's recovery.

551
00:51:52,151 --> 00:51:53,983
We had an agreement!

552
00:51:55,154 --> 00:51:58,943
This meeting was to
be merely a formality.

553
00:51:59,033 --> 00:52:04,403
-Please sit down.
-I'd rather stand. Give me an answer.

554
00:52:04,538 --> 00:52:10,033
The Immobiliare has its roots in the
European tradition. Please understand.

555
00:52:10,836 --> 00:52:14,204
I understand.
Your tactics are despicable.

556
00:52:14,298 --> 00:52:17,381
That's quite an indictment,
coming from a Corleone.

557
00:52:17,509 --> 00:52:21,798
-Gentlemen, gentlemen!
-Remember you are in the Vatican.

558
00:52:25,726 --> 00:52:31,392
-What is it that you want?
-Yes, you will take control.

559
00:52:32,524 --> 00:52:35,983
We'll gladly put you at
the helm of our little fleet,

560
00:52:36,570 --> 00:52:40,404
but our ships must all
sail in the same direction.

561
00:52:42,034 --> 00:52:47,575
Otherwise, who can say how
long your stay with us will last?

562
00:52:48,207 --> 00:52:49,743
[SNORTS]

563
00:52:49,833 --> 00:52:55,704
It's not personal. It's only business.
You should know, Godfather.

564
00:52:59,718 --> 00:53:01,049
Very well.

565
00:53:02,429 --> 00:53:07,424
You want to do business with me?
I will do business with you.

566
00:53:08,435 --> 00:53:10,392
MICHAEL: Vipers, all of them.

567
00:53:16,443 --> 00:53:19,526
-We're back with the Borgias!
-Uncle Michael…

568
00:53:19,613 --> 00:53:22,947
-Andrew!
-I heard you were here.

569
00:53:23,033 --> 00:53:26,571
It's so nice to see you.
Vincent, it's so nice.

570
00:53:27,454 --> 00:53:30,788
ANDREW: What is this about the Borgias?
Those days are over.

571
00:53:36,255 --> 00:53:38,292
-VINCENT: Recognize it?
-MARY: Yeah.

572
00:53:39,967 --> 00:53:45,963
Genco Olive Oil. That's where our
grandfather started as a delivery boy.

573
00:53:46,098 --> 00:53:48,385
Three years later he owned it.

574
00:53:48,475 --> 00:53:50,716
-Only in America.
-That's it.

575
00:53:51,770 --> 00:53:56,890
Vincenzo, where have you been hiding?
We need your help so badly.

576
00:53:56,984 --> 00:54:00,648
-What can I do for you?
-Get rid of Joe Zasa. He sells drugs…

577
00:54:00,779 --> 00:54:05,819
Now that I'm an older woman,
I'm afraid to go out at night.

578
00:54:05,909 --> 00:54:08,241
Where should they be now?

579
00:54:08,328 --> 00:54:11,446
-Lou, what's going on?
-We're late.

580
00:54:13,500 --> 00:54:16,162
-Have I ever let you down?
-I trust you.

581
00:54:16,253 --> 00:54:18,585
-Don't worry.
-Thank you.

582
00:54:18,672 --> 00:54:20,413
Enjoy yourselves.

583
00:54:27,139 --> 00:54:30,848
-What was that?
-The neighborhood's in trouble.

584
00:54:31,977 --> 00:54:34,765
-Do you keep an eye out for them?
-Yes.

585
00:54:34,855 --> 00:54:37,472
-And for me?
-From now on.

586
00:54:38,692 --> 00:54:42,651
-I've missed you all this time.
-I missed you too, cousin.

587
00:54:42,780 --> 00:54:47,525
I missed growing up with my cousins.
I didn't even know you, but missed you.

588
00:54:48,827 --> 00:54:53,367
Do you remember stories about our fathers?
The old days?

589
00:54:53,499 --> 00:54:55,866
Yeah, what do you want to know?

590
00:54:58,170 --> 00:55:03,506
-What was Sonny like?
-Well, he was the Prince of the City.

591
00:55:05,052 --> 00:55:08,716
He died before I was born,
but I've heard a lot about him.

592
00:55:10,474 --> 00:55:13,967
-What about my father?
-He's a great man.

593
00:55:15,479 --> 00:55:17,891
He's a hero. He saved the family.

594
00:55:19,900 --> 00:55:21,641
-Vincent?
-What?

595
00:55:21,735 --> 00:55:23,976
Did he kill his own brother?

596
00:55:28,325 --> 00:55:29,486
No.

597
00:55:32,037 --> 00:55:33,744
So, it's all lies?

598
00:55:38,335 --> 00:55:41,498
Just stories, sweetheart. Okay?

599
00:55:45,592 --> 00:55:46,832
Okay.

600
00:55:48,595 --> 00:55:50,211
I believe you.

601
00:55:51,431 --> 00:55:54,765
-I'm glad you're around.
-I'm glad you're here too.

602
00:55:59,690 --> 00:56:01,180
<i>Cugina…</i>

603
00:56:02,192 --> 00:56:03,603
Cous…

604
00:56:17,958 --> 00:56:21,622
I'd like to take Joey Zasa
for a ride in this and drop him.

605
00:56:21,753 --> 00:56:23,915
Joey Zasa is nothing.

606
00:56:24,798 --> 00:56:28,541
He's a small time enforcer.
He bluffs and threatens.

607
00:56:28,635 --> 00:56:32,378
He's nothing.
You can see him coming a mile away.

608
00:56:33,307 --> 00:56:35,924
-We should kill him before he…
-MICHAEL: No!

609
00:56:39,104 --> 00:56:43,223
Never hate your enemies.
It affects your judgment.

610
00:56:59,583 --> 00:57:02,200
Nice to see you again, Mr. Corleone.

611
00:57:05,547 --> 00:57:07,288
[BAND PLAYING JAZZ]

612
00:57:20,312 --> 00:57:22,178
[MUSIC STOPS]

613
00:57:22,272 --> 00:57:24,639
Hey, girls. Let's go.

614
00:57:39,206 --> 00:57:40,822
[SHUSHING]

615
00:57:42,793 --> 00:57:47,162
We trusted you to manage
our money in the casinos.

616
00:57:47,255 --> 00:57:53,171
It's not even 20 years. You've sold the
casinos and made fortunes for all of us.

617
00:57:53,261 --> 00:57:55,423
Bravo, Don Corleone!

618
00:57:55,514 --> 00:57:57,551
[ALL AGREEING IN ITALIAN]

619
00:57:57,641 --> 00:57:59,052
Thank you.

620
00:58:00,018 --> 00:58:06,731
Friends, I have come here because
our business together is done.

621
00:58:08,402 --> 00:58:10,143
We have prospered,

622
00:58:10,237 --> 00:58:15,357
and now it is time for us to dissolve
the business relationship between us.

623
00:58:17,619 --> 00:58:19,155
That's it.

624
00:58:19,246 --> 00:58:22,489
But I do have a little surprise. Al?

625
00:58:25,627 --> 00:58:27,743
Your shares in the casinos.

626
00:58:28,422 --> 00:58:32,422
I thought I cut through all the red tape,
so you could get your money right away.

627
00:58:32,509 --> 00:58:35,046
[MEN CHATTERING IN ITALIAN]

628
00:58:38,849 --> 00:58:41,181
50 million dollars!

629
00:58:41,309 --> 00:58:44,768
-MICHAEL: Not everybody gets the same.
-Nothing for you…

630
00:58:44,896 --> 00:58:49,891
-MICHAEL: It depends on your investment.
-MAN: Michael, this is really generous!

631
00:58:50,944 --> 00:58:52,355
Wonderful!

632
00:58:52,446 --> 00:58:53,652
[MAN WHISTLING]

633
00:58:53,739 --> 00:58:55,321
[THANKS IN ITALIAN]

634
00:58:55,407 --> 00:58:59,947
-Parisi, how much did you invest?
-I don't remember.

635
00:59:00,746 --> 00:59:02,453
You're blessed.

636
00:59:07,419 --> 00:59:12,164
My family has done much of
the hard work, taken many risks.

637
00:59:14,426 --> 00:59:17,589
All to make money for
the rest of the families.

638
00:59:19,973 --> 00:59:22,010
You all know Joey Zasa.

639
00:59:22,976 --> 00:59:25,434
He is, I admit, an important man.

640
00:59:26,438 --> 00:59:30,181
His picture is on the cover of
the New York Times magazine.

641
00:59:30,859 --> 00:59:34,727
He gets the Esquire Magazine
award for the best dressed gangster.

642
00:59:34,821 --> 00:59:35,982
[MEN CHUCKLING SOFTLY]

643
00:59:36,073 --> 00:59:37,984
The newspapers praise him

644
00:59:38,075 --> 00:59:42,615
because he hires Blacks,
which shows he has a good heart.

645
00:59:45,248 --> 00:59:46,864
He is famous.

646
00:59:47,626 --> 00:59:53,793
Who knows? Maybe one day
he'll make all of you popular.

647
00:59:53,882 --> 00:59:55,372
[MEN MURMURING]

648
00:59:55,467 --> 00:59:56,628
It's true.

649
00:59:56,718 --> 01:00:02,384
I make more of a <i>bella figura.</i>
That is my nature.

650
01:00:02,474 --> 01:00:07,514
But I also want to make a
move into legitimate enterprises.

651
01:00:07,604 --> 01:00:10,312
I'd like a little pin from the Pope.

652
01:00:10,816 --> 01:00:15,902
Sure, I take the Blacks and
the Spanish into my family,

653
01:00:15,987 --> 01:00:19,480
because that's America.

654
01:00:20,200 --> 01:00:23,568
And you guarantee that
they don't deal drugs?

655
01:00:25,413 --> 01:00:30,032
I don't guarantee that. I guarantee
that I'll kill anybody who does.

656
01:00:34,714 --> 01:00:39,834
-[SOFTLY] Let me talk to him.
-Who can refuse Don Altobello?

657
01:00:40,345 --> 01:00:42,632
-Joey, are you…
-No!

658
01:00:43,431 --> 01:00:48,767
I say to all of you, I have been
treated this day with no respect.

659
01:00:49,938 --> 01:00:55,433
I've earned you all money.
I've made you rich and I asked for little.

660
01:00:55,527 --> 01:00:59,361
Good. You will not give, so I'll take!

661
01:01:00,699 --> 01:01:03,236
As for Don Corleone,

662
01:01:03,326 --> 01:01:09,288
he makes it very clear to
me today that he is my enemy.

663
01:01:13,253 --> 01:01:15,460
You must choose between us.

664
01:01:17,007 --> 01:01:18,748
[MEN MUTTERING]

665
01:01:20,135 --> 01:01:21,296
ALTOBELLO: No, Joey!

666
01:01:22,888 --> 01:01:25,596
Michael, we could reason together.

667
01:01:26,183 --> 01:01:27,548
No.

668
01:01:28,894 --> 01:01:32,888
Michael, please… let's agree.

669
01:01:33,523 --> 01:01:37,353
He doesn't know what he's… No, no.

670
01:01:42,407 --> 01:01:45,149
PARISI: Michael, the news is everywhere.

671
01:01:46,077 --> 01:01:50,162
Everyone says that
you control Immobiliare.

672
01:01:50,290 --> 01:01:55,376
MAN: Immobiliare is already
laundering money in Peru and Nassau.

673
01:01:56,630 --> 01:02:01,090
We've worked with you for 40 years.
We should wet our beaks a little.

674
01:02:01,176 --> 01:02:06,091
-We want to do business with you.
-That's right, we've been together…

675
01:02:06,181 --> 01:02:08,013
[RUMBLING]

676
01:02:16,107 --> 01:02:19,395
-It's a hit! Let's go!
-MAN: Let's get out of here! Move!

677
01:02:20,570 --> 01:02:22,607
[HELICOPTER WHIRRING]

678
01:02:25,325 --> 01:02:27,157
[MACHINE GUN FIRING]

679
01:02:38,672 --> 01:02:41,164
My coat! It's my lucky coat!

680
01:02:42,342 --> 01:02:44,174
It's my lucky coat!

681
01:02:44,261 --> 01:02:45,296
[GROANING]

682
01:02:50,350 --> 01:02:51,761
Stay behind me!

683
01:02:52,018 --> 01:02:54,510
[MACHINE GUN FIRING]

684
01:03:07,867 --> 01:03:10,029
Mikey, this way!

685
01:03:18,461 --> 01:03:21,670
Zasa, you son-of-a-bitch…

686
01:03:25,385 --> 01:03:27,217
[ALARM CLANGING]

687
01:03:31,224 --> 01:03:33,215
[SIRENS APPROACHING]

688
01:03:36,980 --> 01:03:38,812
[GLASS SHATTERING]

689
01:03:42,193 --> 01:03:44,480
Come on. We're out of here.

690
01:03:48,366 --> 01:03:51,529
[HORN BLARING RHYTHMICALLY]

691
01:04:13,767 --> 01:04:15,599
[THUNDER RUMBLING]

692
01:04:16,686 --> 01:04:19,018
-MICHAEL: You did good, Vincent.
<i>-Grazie.</i>

693
01:04:19,397 --> 01:04:22,606
NERI: The old Dons were
pretty much wiped out.

694
01:04:22,734 --> 01:04:26,022
The survivors made deals with Zasa.

695
01:04:27,197 --> 01:04:29,609
-Altobello?
-He survived.

696
01:04:29,741 --> 01:04:34,611
He's with his daughters in Staten Island.
He says he's going to retire in Sicily.

697
01:04:36,539 --> 01:04:41,033
Joey Zasa would never pull
something like this without the backing.

698
01:04:41,878 --> 01:04:47,544
He's just muscle. He doesn't have
the wit for that helicopter attack.

699
01:04:47,634 --> 01:04:52,049
He doesn't even have the ambition
to wipe out the whole Commission.

700
01:04:52,138 --> 01:04:54,880
I say we hit back and take Zasa out!

701
01:04:56,267 --> 01:04:58,634
[MAN REPORTING EVENTS ON TV]

702
01:05:00,480 --> 01:05:03,472
[WHISPERING] Never let
anyone know what you're thinking.

703
01:05:11,449 --> 01:05:14,441
Let's get a message to Joey Zasa.

704
01:05:17,664 --> 01:05:19,996
I respect what he's done.

705
01:05:21,126 --> 01:05:23,993
The new overthrows the old. It's natural.

706
01:05:24,504 --> 01:05:27,121
How can you do business with this guy?

707
01:05:29,592 --> 01:05:33,551
I'm a businessman, first and foremost.
I want no further conflict.

708
01:05:33,680 --> 01:05:38,095
-Tell him that he can live or he can die.
-Vincent, will you shut up!

709
01:05:56,661 --> 01:05:58,151
That's it.

710
01:06:00,373 --> 01:06:01,863
Joey Zasa…

711
01:06:02,542 --> 01:06:04,954
He can't be doing this alone.

712
01:06:08,715 --> 01:06:12,629
Just when I thought I was
out, they pull me back in.

713
01:06:21,394 --> 01:06:27,060
Our true enemy has
not yet shown his face.

714
01:06:31,404 --> 01:06:32,690
Michael!

715
01:06:33,490 --> 01:06:35,151
[MICHAEL GASPING]

716
