01:32:16,448 --> 01:32:19,907
-I love my family.
-Even your cousin Vincent?

954
01:32:24,122 --> 01:32:26,033
I really love him.

955
01:32:27,459 --> 01:32:30,622
-He's your first cousin.
-Then I love him first.

956
01:32:31,755 --> 01:32:34,292
Mary, you can't see him.

957
01:32:35,133 --> 01:32:37,374
Just don't see him anymore.

958
01:32:38,386 --> 01:32:41,549
He's right. It's too dangerous.

959
01:32:44,059 --> 01:32:46,221
Mary, you can't see him anymore.

960
01:32:46,311 --> 01:32:47,392
[BELL TOLLING]

961
01:32:47,479 --> 01:32:49,641
-Not in that fashion.
-No.

962
01:32:51,399 --> 01:32:54,733
-Please, promise me.
-No!

963
01:32:54,819 --> 01:32:57,151
-Obey me on this.
-No, Dad!

964
01:33:02,577 --> 01:33:06,571
Mary is smart, Dad.
She'll understand eventually.

965
01:33:08,958 --> 01:33:11,495
[POP SONG BLARING ON RADIO]

966
01:33:29,813 --> 01:33:32,430
<i>Bella cugina… Tesoro mio.</i>

967
01:33:44,035 --> 01:33:46,322
-You wanted to see me?
-Yeah.

968
01:33:47,288 --> 01:33:50,531
I want you to do something for me.
It's dangerous.

969
01:33:52,377 --> 01:33:55,620
Good. I'm in. What do you need?

970
01:33:56,464 --> 01:33:59,547
I want you to sell your
soul to Don Altobello.

971
01:34:00,343 --> 01:34:02,004
To betray me.

972
01:34:05,390 --> 01:34:07,381
He'd never believe me.

973
01:34:08,476 --> 01:34:10,843
-That depends.
-VINCENT: Sit down.

974
01:34:13,731 --> 01:34:15,313
I have an idea.

975
01:34:17,026 --> 01:34:20,394
See if you can learn how
high Altobello is connected.

976
01:34:24,701 --> 01:34:26,487
Arrange a meeting.

977
01:34:29,164 --> 01:34:33,579
You say how devoted you are to me.
Tell him your problems.

978
01:34:34,752 --> 01:34:37,540
-Ask for his help.
-What problems?

979
01:34:39,674 --> 01:34:42,541
That you want to run
away with my daughter.

980
01:34:43,261 --> 01:34:46,754
But you know that if you
do, I will become your enemy.

981
01:34:52,020 --> 01:34:55,354
-You know that I would never do that.
-I know.

982
01:34:56,733 --> 01:35:01,102
<i>Ask Altobello to speak to me.
To further the marriage.</i>

983
01:35:01,905 --> 01:35:06,570
But you're cousins, after all.
Michael was always a little old-fashioned.

984
01:35:07,952 --> 01:35:12,867
Say you can't belong to my legitimate
world. That you want your own family.

985
01:35:13,625 --> 01:35:16,959
I could straighten out
what Joey Zasa left behind.

986
01:35:18,546 --> 01:35:21,538
If you could use your
friendship to persuade him,

987
01:35:22,550 --> 01:35:25,463
I would be indebted to you forever.

988
01:35:27,430 --> 01:35:31,048
A Corleone knows the
value of such a friend.

989
01:35:32,894 --> 01:35:35,306
Then you would work for me?

990
01:35:36,147 --> 01:35:37,387
<i>Si.</i>

991
01:35:40,068 --> 01:35:42,730
<i>Bacio la mano, Don Altobello.</i>

992
01:35:45,823 --> 01:35:50,818
If he hints that he wants
you to betray me, get insulted,

993
01:35:51,454 --> 01:35:53,491
because that's his trap.

994
01:36:00,213 --> 01:36:03,376
You're not telling me
the whole truth, Vincenzo.

995
01:36:06,636 --> 01:36:12,302
Isn't it true, that with Michael
gone, the girl controls everything?

996
01:36:16,562 --> 01:36:20,226
-Leave the girl out of this.
-Of course, you love her.

997
01:36:20,358 --> 01:36:22,019
And she loves you.

998
01:36:42,755 --> 01:36:45,918
I guessed it, didn't I?

999
01:36:47,427 --> 01:36:52,263
You're a wise man, Don Altobello.
I'll be learning a lot from you.

1000
01:36:53,349 --> 01:36:57,058
The richest man is the one
with the most powerful friends.

1001
01:36:59,522 --> 01:37:02,264
It's my duty to make the introductions.

1002
01:37:04,777 --> 01:37:06,609
[GREETS RESPECTFULLY IN ITALIAN]

1003
01:37:09,032 --> 01:37:11,114
Don Lucchesi.

1004
01:37:13,745 --> 01:37:19,457
Don Altobello tells me that you have
a strong character. A man of respect.

1005
01:37:19,584 --> 01:37:22,918
This is the hero who put
Joey Zasa in his grave.

1006
01:37:23,421 --> 01:37:27,289
If we'd known of his existence,
we wouldn't have backed Joey.

1007
01:37:27,717 --> 01:37:29,754
No one wants another Joe.

1008
01:37:31,929 --> 01:37:34,045
Let me be your friend.

1009
01:37:34,557 --> 01:37:38,642
-Even the strongest man needs friends.
-I'm flattered.

1010
01:37:40,104 --> 01:37:44,598
You're a man of finance and politics.
Things I don't understand.

1011
01:37:45,109 --> 01:37:46,224
[SCOFFS]

1012
01:37:46,319 --> 01:37:50,278
You understand guns. Finance is a gun.

1013
01:37:51,449 --> 01:37:55,659
Politics is knowing
when to pull the trigger.

1014
01:38:00,249 --> 01:38:01,330
How can I help?

1015
01:38:01,459 --> 01:38:02,494
[CHUCKLES KNOWINGLY]

1016
01:38:02,627 --> 01:38:03,958
<i>Vieni?</i>

1017
01:38:07,006 --> 01:38:11,375
Blessed is the peacemaker, for
he can be called the child of God.

1018
01:38:11,469 --> 01:38:12,594
[BOTH CHATTERING IN ITALIAN]

1019
01:38:12,678 --> 01:38:15,466
<i>-Tu parli Italiano un poco?
-Sì.</i>

1020
01:38:37,870 --> 01:38:40,703
NERI: [IN ITALIAN] The
wheelchair, for Don Tommasino.

1021
01:38:40,832 --> 01:38:42,664
[SPEAKING ITALIAN]

1022
01:38:48,673 --> 01:38:51,800
MICHAEL: I trusted this business
arrangement with the Archbishop.

1023
01:38:51,884 --> 01:38:53,466
I trusted him.

1024
01:38:53,553 --> 01:38:56,671
I was sure his honesty
was beyond a doubt.

1025
01:38:57,682 --> 01:39:01,892
But, as you see, I'm now
the victim of a swindle.

1026
01:39:02,895 --> 01:39:08,516
He's stalling me. Vast monies have
gone to people in high political places

1027
01:39:08,860 --> 01:39:11,818
and the Vatican Bank is the guarantor.

1028
01:39:11,904 --> 01:39:17,070
CARDINAL: If what you say is
true, there will be a great scandal.

1029
01:39:19,245 --> 01:39:24,285
Look at this stone. It has been
in the water for a very long time,

1030
01:39:24,375 --> 01:39:28,118
but the water has not penetrated it.

1031
01:39:32,383 --> 01:39:33,623
Look…

1032
01:39:34,719 --> 01:39:39,839
Perfectly dry. The same thing
has happened to men in Europe.

1033
01:39:39,932 --> 01:39:44,051
For centuries they have been
surrounded by Christianity,

1034
01:39:44,896 --> 01:39:50,767
but Christ has not penetrated.
Christ doesn't live within them.

1035
01:39:53,070 --> 01:39:54,560
[GASPING]

1036
01:39:54,906 --> 01:39:59,070
-What's happening?
-Could you get me something sweet?

1037
01:39:59,160 --> 01:40:02,494
Some orange juice, candy…

1038
01:40:03,247 --> 01:40:06,114
[ORDERING FOOD IN ITALIAN]

1039
01:40:06,250 --> 01:40:08,491
I have trouble with diabetes.

1040
01:40:12,256 --> 01:40:14,543
[GASPING] My blood sugar goes low.

1041
01:40:14,634 --> 01:40:16,420
I understand.

1042
01:40:23,518 --> 01:40:25,429
[THANKS IN ITALIAN]

1043
01:40:39,700 --> 01:40:42,613
It happens sometimes
when I'm under stress.

1044
01:40:43,496 --> 01:40:45,112
I understand.

1045
01:40:47,208 --> 01:40:50,951
To come to you on such a delicate matter…

1046
01:40:53,798 --> 01:40:58,338
Accusations against your Archbishop.
It was difficult for me.

1047
01:41:00,137 --> 01:41:01,844
The mind suffers

1048
01:41:02,348 --> 01:41:05,136
and the body cries out.

1049
01:41:11,315 --> 01:41:12,805
That's true.

1050
01:41:14,485 --> 01:41:18,319
Would you like to make your confession?

1051
01:41:22,076 --> 01:41:23,737
[CHUCKLES]

1052
01:41:25,037 --> 01:41:26,903
Your Eminence, I'm…

1053
01:41:31,252 --> 01:41:36,668
It's been so long. I wouldn't..
. I wouldn't know where to…

1054
01:41:38,217 --> 01:41:40,083
It's been 30 years.

1055
01:41:42,013 --> 01:41:44,675
I'd use up too much
of your time, I think.

1056
01:41:45,600 --> 01:41:48,183
I always have time to save souls.

1057
01:41:49,770 --> 01:41:54,389
-Well, I'm beyond redemption.
-No, no…

1058
01:41:56,360 --> 01:41:58,192
[SPEAKING ITALIAN]

1059
01:42:03,784 --> 01:42:07,527
I hear the confessions
of my own priests here.

1060
01:42:08,873 --> 01:42:12,366
Sometimes the desire to
confess is overwhelming,

1061
01:42:13,085 --> 01:42:15,452
and we must seize the moment.

1062
01:42:20,134 --> 01:42:23,798
What is the point of
confessing if I don't repent?

1063
01:42:26,390 --> 01:42:28,757
I hear you are a practical man.

1064
01:42:29,727 --> 01:42:31,764
What have you got to lose?

1065
01:42:43,658 --> 01:42:45,069
Go on.

1066
01:42:51,791 --> 01:42:54,290
[SIGHS] I… [CLEARING THROAT]

1067
01:42:54,418 --> 01:42:56,250
…betrayed my wife.

1068
01:42:58,005 --> 01:42:59,541
Go on, my son.

1069
01:42:59,632 --> 01:43:01,748
[BELL TOLLING]

1070
01:43:05,262 --> 01:43:07,003
I betrayed myself.

1071
01:43:10,101 --> 01:43:11,591
I killed men.

1072
01:43:15,690 --> 01:43:18,102
And I ordered men to be killed.

1073
01:43:19,652 --> 01:43:21,768
Go on, my son. Go on.

1074
01:43:27,868 --> 01:43:29,450
It's useless.

1075
01:43:31,038 --> 01:43:32,699
Go on, my son.

1076
01:43:34,125 --> 01:43:35,615
I killed…

1077
01:43:40,715 --> 01:43:43,207
I ordered the death of my brother.

1078
01:43:44,385 --> 01:43:46,126
He injured me.

1079
01:43:47,805 --> 01:43:49,842
I killed my mother's son.

1080
01:43:51,684 --> 01:43:53,721
[SOBBING] I killed my father's son.

1081
01:43:56,647 --> 01:43:58,979
[WEEPING QUIETLY]

1082
01:44:04,488 --> 01:44:08,903
Your sins are terrible,
and it is just that you suffer.

1083
01:44:10,494 --> 01:44:12,906
Your life could be redeemed,

1084
01:44:14,331 --> 01:44:18,165
but I know that you don't believe that.
You will not change.

1085
01:44:19,670 --> 01:44:21,206
[CONTINUES SOBBING]

1086
01:44:22,381 --> 01:44:24,213
[ABSOLVING IN LATIN]

1087
01:44:33,559 --> 01:44:36,597
[BELL TOLLING]

1088
01:44:41,942 --> 01:44:44,684
[REPORTER TALKING
SOMBERLY IN ITALIAN ON RADIO]

1089
01:44:48,783 --> 01:44:53,778
<i>Pope Paul VI, Supreme Pontiff
of the Roman Catholic Church…</i>

1090
01:44:54,079 --> 01:44:57,288
<i>Died last night at 9:40 p.m.</i>

1091
01:44:57,875 --> 01:45:01,118
<i>The Pope was 81 years old…</i>

1092
01:45:02,087 --> 01:45:05,625
<i>And had been in poor health
for the last several months.</i>

1093
01:45:10,387 --> 01:45:11,752
Connie…

1094
01:45:13,599 --> 01:45:17,968
All my life I've kept
trying to go up in society.

1095
01:45:18,646 --> 01:45:21,559
To where everything
higher up was legal, straight…

1096
01:45:23,651 --> 01:45:27,144
But the higher I go, the
more crooked it becomes.

1097
01:45:29,907 --> 01:45:32,069
Where the hell does it end?

1098
01:45:37,832 --> 01:45:39,288
[SIGHS]

1099
01:45:41,126 --> 01:45:44,585
They've been killing each
other for centuries here.

1100
01:45:46,006 --> 01:45:50,091
For money, for pride, for family.

1101
01:45:53,264 --> 01:45:57,258
To keep from becoming the
slaves of the rich <i>pezzi da novanta.</i>

1102
01:46:04,358 --> 01:46:06,599
I made confession, Connie.

1103
01:46:07,611 --> 01:46:09,693
I confessed my sins.

1104
01:46:11,365 --> 01:46:16,451
Why? That's not like you. You don't
have to confess your sins to a stranger.

1105
01:46:17,371 --> 01:46:18,953
It was the man.

1106
01:46:19,957 --> 01:46:23,666
He's a good man. A true priest.

1107
01:46:27,840 --> 01:46:29,877
He can change things.

1108
01:46:32,136 --> 01:46:33,877
Michael…

1109
01:46:35,347 --> 01:46:39,215
You know, sometimes
I think of poor Fredo.

1110
01:46:40,060 --> 01:46:43,348
Drowned. It was God's will.

1111
01:46:45,900 --> 01:46:48,141
It was a terrible accident.

1112
01:46:49,570 --> 01:46:51,481
But it's finished.

1113
01:46:56,535 --> 01:46:58,367
Michael, I love you.

1114
01:47:00,748 --> 01:47:02,705
I'll always help you.

1115
01:47:09,673 --> 01:47:12,005
[CRYING QUIETLY]

1116
01:47:15,012 --> 01:47:16,502
Oh, Connie…

1117
01:47:42,706 --> 01:47:44,447
[GREETING IN ITALIAN]

1118
01:47:46,460 --> 01:47:49,327
[IN ITALIAN] I am honored, Don Altobello,

1119
01:47:49,421 --> 01:47:53,460
that you've come from
Palermo to visit me.

1120
01:47:56,804 --> 01:48:01,799
[IN ITALIAN] Hey, the little kid!
He's grown.

1121
01:48:02,393 --> 01:48:04,225
Do the donkey for me.

1122
01:48:06,647 --> 01:48:08,638
[BRAYING]

1123
01:48:15,155 --> 01:48:17,487
[NICKERS]

1124
01:48:21,829 --> 01:48:25,914
It's been some time since
we did business together.

1125
01:48:29,837 --> 01:48:34,832
You are my "ace in the
hole," as we say in America.

1126
01:48:34,925 --> 01:48:40,796
I have a stone in my shoe.
You can remove it.

1127
01:48:48,105 --> 01:48:50,972
Only one stone?

1128
01:48:53,027 --> 01:48:58,943
It's dangerous. A famous man.

1129
01:48:59,199 --> 01:49:02,692
You will have to take precautions.

1130
01:49:05,539 --> 01:49:11,000
Tell me what to do.
Then I will tell you my price.

1131
01:49:15,215 --> 01:49:18,003
Ah, what bread!

1132
01:49:22,056 --> 01:49:26,220
Olive oil…

1133
01:49:29,396 --> 01:49:32,889
Virgin… only in Sicily.

1134
01:49:35,360 --> 01:49:36,600
<i>Alla salute!</i>

1135
01:49:36,695 --> 01:49:39,562
[SCOFFS] To death.

1136
01:49:40,741 --> 01:49:43,028
[MAN CHATTERING IN ITALIAN OVER PA]

1137
01:49:53,087 --> 01:49:54,703
Kay!

1138
01:49:54,838 --> 01:49:57,079
-Connie!
-How are you?

1139
01:49:57,174 --> 01:50:00,257
Mary, I've missed you.

1140
01:50:00,761 --> 01:50:04,504
-Hello, Michael.
-Mom, look at this.

1141
01:50:06,100 --> 01:50:07,135
[GASPING]

1142
01:50:07,226 --> 01:50:08,476
[CHUCKLING IN AMAZEMENT]

1143
01:50:08,560 --> 01:50:14,476
-It's too bad Douglas couldn't come.
-I know. He had a very important trial.

1144
01:50:14,566 --> 01:50:16,557
I know he wanted to come.

1145
01:50:17,736 --> 01:50:19,773
-The car is…
-Okay.

1146
01:50:21,740 --> 01:50:27,907
-Well, your son is an artist.
-Oh, yes. Thanks to you.

1147
01:50:28,580 --> 01:50:32,915
-What for?
-For making me let him go.

1148
01:50:33,627 --> 01:50:38,667
Well, after all these years, here
I am in Sicily for the first time.

1149
01:50:38,799 --> 01:50:41,917
-I want to get a picture of you together.
-Okay.

1150
01:50:43,887 --> 01:50:45,628
Hey, Dad. Smile!

1151
01:50:50,144 --> 01:50:53,057
I see you still have Al Neri. Why?

1152
01:50:54,273 --> 01:50:57,766
I need him.
He helps me get in and out of the car.

1153
01:50:57,901 --> 01:50:58,982
[STIFLING LAUGHTER]

1154
01:50:59,069 --> 01:51:02,778
-He carries my briefcase.
-You're still a liar, Michael.

1155
01:51:04,074 --> 01:51:09,285
Let me show you Sicily, the real Sicily.
So you'll understand the family history.

1156
01:51:10,414 --> 01:51:13,247
I think I understand it well enough.

1157
01:51:42,112 --> 01:51:44,319
[SPEAKING ITALIAN]

1158
01:52:04,885 --> 01:52:10,847
Anthony, I have something you
made for me a very long time ago.

1159
01:52:12,559 --> 01:52:15,347
-Might bring you luck.
-Thanks.

1160
01:52:19,566 --> 01:52:22,809
You saved it… I remember.

1161
01:52:26,823 --> 01:52:28,359
Thank you, Dad.

1162
01:52:29,993 --> 01:52:31,734
I'm proud of you.

1163
01:52:32,496 --> 01:52:34,032
Thank you.

1164
01:52:39,586 --> 01:52:41,543
[FOOTSTEPS APPROACHING]

1165
01:52:41,672 --> 01:52:43,333
[FOOTSTEPS STOP]

1166
01:52:50,347 --> 01:52:53,135
-Are they as good as they look?
-Better.

1167
01:52:53,225 --> 01:52:57,685
They're the best. As long as they
are around, Uncle Michael is safe.

1168
01:52:58,355 --> 01:52:59,891
MARY: Goodbye.

1169
01:53:02,526 --> 01:53:05,735
-Tell your father I'll be back for dinner.
-Okay.

1170
01:53:06,238 --> 01:53:08,855
-Have fun.
-Tell Tony to wait for me.

1171
01:53:08,949 --> 01:53:10,405
I will.

1172
01:53:12,911 --> 01:53:16,495
<i>Buongiorno, signora.</i> At your service.

1173
01:53:16,581 --> 01:53:17,946
[SNORTS IN SURPRISE]

1174
01:53:20,460 --> 01:53:23,373
If I see Dad, I'll tell him you left.

1175
01:53:28,885 --> 01:53:32,549
You're the only one left
with my father's strength.

1176
01:53:34,766 --> 01:53:38,725
If anything happens to
Michael, I want you to strike back.

1177
01:53:41,606 --> 01:53:43,768
I'll have everything ready.

1178
01:53:47,237 --> 01:53:48,944
Do you swear?

1179
01:53:56,288 --> 01:53:57,904
I swear to you.

1180
01:54:28,278 --> 01:54:29,939
Here it is.

1181
01:54:31,698 --> 01:54:34,315
The house where my father was born.

1182
01:54:35,452 --> 01:54:40,822
This is where they came to take
him when he was a boy. To kill him.

1183
01:54:42,793 --> 01:54:43,918
[TRADITIONAL MUSIC PLAYING]

1184
01:54:44,002 --> 01:54:45,788
Wait…

1185
01:54:46,505 --> 01:54:48,462
Listen to that.

1186
01:55:07,651 --> 01:55:09,642
You know Mary's in love.

1187
01:55:11,154 --> 01:55:12,736
Yes, I know.

1188
01:55:13,990 --> 01:55:17,824
With a handsome young
Italian man with dark eyes…

1189
01:55:19,246 --> 01:55:21,078
I won't allow it.

1190
01:55:23,875 --> 01:55:27,493
It's wrong.
It's wrong and it's dangerous.

1191
01:55:27,712 --> 01:55:30,704
[IN ITALIAN] "Oh father, my father!"

1192
01:55:31,383 --> 01:55:33,750
"Give me some time to pray to the Lord."

1193
01:55:34,886 --> 01:55:38,004
The Baroness of Carini
had betrayed her husband…

1194
01:55:38,557 --> 01:55:41,345
And fallen in love with her cousin.

1195
01:55:41,726 --> 01:55:43,808
"There will be no forgiveness!"

1196
01:55:44,062 --> 01:55:47,680
Her father stabbed her through the heart.

1197
01:55:48,650 --> 01:55:49,640
[EXCLAIMS]

1198
01:55:49,734 --> 01:55:51,284
[CONTINUES RECITING IN ITALIAN]

1199
01:55:52,696 --> 01:55:54,858
[WHIMPERING IN ITALIAN]

1200
01:55:56,741 --> 01:55:59,199
[NARRATOR CONTINUES]

1201
01:55:59,911 --> 01:56:01,401
Honor, huh?

1202
01:56:21,057 --> 01:56:24,095
I remember the time you
came to my parents' house

1203
01:56:24,227 --> 01:56:27,765
and told me about the family business.

1204
01:56:27,898 --> 01:56:32,859
How you'd never have anything to
do with it. You sounded like Tony.

1205
01:56:33,904 --> 01:56:35,895
I was a lot like Tony.

1206
01:56:43,538 --> 01:56:46,371
-I can barely see him… Kay?
-What?

1207
01:56:46,458 --> 01:56:49,120
-Do you mind driving?
-What's wrong?

1208
01:56:49,252 --> 01:56:52,210
My eyes.
Sometimes they're all right, but…

1209
01:56:53,924 --> 01:56:56,256
I have to see Don Tommasino…

1210
01:56:56,384 --> 01:56:57,374
[SPEAKING ITALIAN]

1211
01:56:57,469 --> 01:56:58,675
[YELPS]

1212
01:56:58,762 --> 01:56:59,843
[LAUGHING IN SHOCK]

1213
01:56:59,930 --> 01:57:01,386
Well…

1214
01:57:02,599 --> 01:57:05,933
-There are no bodyguards today.
-I really snuck away.

1215
01:57:13,109 --> 01:57:17,569
[IN ITALIAN] Father, where are you going?
Would you like a ride?

1216
01:57:17,989 --> 01:57:19,900
[BECKONING IN ITALIAN]

1217
01:57:26,665 --> 01:57:30,954
I know you. You're Mosca of Montelepre.

1218
01:57:32,087 --> 01:57:35,921
You were an assassin then
and you're an assassin now.

1219
01:57:36,132 --> 01:57:39,466
[IN ITALIAN] I know Michael
Corleone is at your house.

1220
01:57:39,844 --> 01:57:42,085
I will pass through the gates with you.

1221
01:57:42,180 --> 01:57:43,215
[CURSES IN ITALIAN]

1222
01:57:43,306 --> 01:57:44,341
[EXCLAIMS]

1223
01:57:54,693 --> 01:57:56,855
[GREETING IN ITALIAN]

1224
01:57:58,989 --> 01:58:00,775
[IN ENGLISH] How are you?

1225
01:58:00,865 --> 01:58:04,449
This is Calo, one of my
bodyguards in the old days.

1226
01:58:04,536 --> 01:58:06,527
[SPEAKING ITALIAN]

1227
01:58:10,292 --> 01:58:12,875
-We can wait here.
-You want a drink?

1228
01:58:13,169 --> 01:58:15,957
[SPEAKING ITALIAN]

1229
01:58:18,341 --> 01:58:21,174
I spent a lot of time in this room

1230
01:58:22,304 --> 01:58:24,341
thinking of you.

1231
01:58:27,350 --> 01:58:29,512
And then you got married.

1232
01:58:33,148 --> 01:58:36,516
-I still thought of you.
-What's in that room?

1233
01:58:41,323 --> 01:58:44,861
This is dangerous for you.
This is Sicily.

1234
01:58:47,996 --> 01:58:50,363
-I love this country.
-Why?

1235
01:58:52,876 --> 01:58:58,838
Well, all through history, terrible
things have happened to these people.

1236
01:58:59,841 --> 01:59:02,048
Terrible injustices.

1237
01:59:02,927 --> 01:59:07,842
But they still expect good, rather
than bad, will happen to them.

1238
01:59:08,391 --> 01:59:10,723
Sort of like me and you?

1239
01:59:14,564 --> 01:59:17,226
-How so?
-I'm still here, right?

1240
01:59:18,234 --> 01:59:21,272
We do have a bad
history, but I'm still here.

1241
01:59:21,404 --> 01:59:24,066
Yes, you are, but with dread.

1242
01:59:29,037 --> 01:59:30,744
Give me the order!

1243
01:59:31,247 --> 01:59:34,365
Is that supposed to
make me not dread you?

1244
01:59:36,586 --> 01:59:38,793
We're in Sicily. It's opera.

1245
01:59:41,424 --> 01:59:42,880
Okay.

1246
01:59:45,470 --> 01:59:47,256
What do we do now?

1247
01:59:49,974 --> 01:59:53,888
Be reasonable.
Let's try not to hurt each other.

1248
01:59:55,605 --> 01:59:57,095
[SIGHS]

1249
02:00:01,736 --> 02:00:03,773
I want you to forgive me.

1250
02:00:06,574 --> 02:00:09,487
-For what?
-Everything.

1251
02:00:13,248 --> 02:00:15,330
Oh, like God?

1252
02:00:17,252 --> 02:00:19,835
No, I need something a little closer.

1253
02:00:22,757 --> 02:00:25,920
You couldn't understand,
back in those days.

1254
02:00:27,429 --> 02:00:32,299
I loved my father.
I swore I would never be a man like him,

1255
02:00:32,392 --> 02:00:36,135
but I loved him and he was in danger.
What could I do?

1256
02:00:36,813 --> 02:00:39,601
And then later, you were in danger.

1257
02:00:40,483 --> 02:00:43,817
Our children were in danger.
What could I do?

1258
02:00:44,821 --> 02:00:50,112
You were all that I…
loved and valued most in the world.

1259
02:00:52,495 --> 02:00:55,112
Now I'm losing you. I lost you.

1260
02:00:55,832 --> 02:00:57,664
You're gone.

1261
02:00:58,960 --> 02:01:01,748
And it was all for nothing. So…

1262
02:01:06,468 --> 02:01:11,463
You have to understand, I had a
whole different destiny planned.

1263
02:01:15,101 --> 02:01:16,967
All right, I'll stop.

1264
02:01:27,489 --> 02:01:31,448
I really don't know what
you want from me, Michael.

1265
02:01:31,868 --> 02:01:36,032
-I mean…
-I'm not the man that you think I am.

1266
02:01:36,623 --> 02:01:37,784
[RESTRAINING SOBS]

1267
02:01:37,874 --> 02:01:41,162
-I don't know.
-I love you, Kay.

1268
02:01:43,213 --> 02:01:45,170
Don't dread me anymore.

1269
02:01:50,970 --> 02:01:54,838
You know, every night here in Sicily…

1270
02:01:57,018 --> 02:02:02,013
I dream about my wife and my children…

1271
02:02:05,527 --> 02:02:07,484
And how I lost them.

1272
02:02:09,697 --> 02:02:15,409
I guess that if it's any consolation,
I want you to know that…

1273
02:02:18,873 --> 02:02:20,329
That

1274
02:02:21,376 --> 02:02:23,708
I always loved you, Michael.

1275
02:02:25,213 --> 02:02:26,920
And you know

1276
02:02:28,758 --> 02:02:31,170
always, I always will.

1277
02:02:47,443 --> 02:02:48,854
[KNOCK ON DOOR]

1278
02:02:59,747 --> 02:03:02,079
[IN ITALIAN] What is it? What's wrong?

1279
02:03:02,292 --> 02:03:05,125
[IN ITALIAN] They found
Don Tommasino shot.

1280
02:03:06,421 --> 02:03:08,628
MICHAEL: Is he dead?

1281
02:03:10,425 --> 02:03:13,918
My master is dead. Blood calls for blood.

1282
02:03:14,596 --> 02:03:17,429
I must have revenge!

1283
02:03:21,227 --> 02:03:26,438
Someday, you may have to
do a difficult service for me.

1284
02:03:26,649 --> 02:03:28,231
Command me.

1285
02:03:30,111 --> 02:03:31,226
It never ends.

1286
02:03:31,321 --> 02:03:33,483
CALO: I will avenge him!

1287
02:03:39,120 --> 02:03:40,155
[BELLS TOLLING]

1288
02:03:40,246 --> 02:03:42,112
[CARDINAL READING NAMES]

1289
02:03:48,671 --> 02:03:50,161
[IN ITALIAN] Totals…

1290
02:03:52,175 --> 02:03:54,507
Lorscheider, 1 vote.

1291
02:03:55,178 --> 02:03:58,261
Siri, 11 votes.

1292
02:03:58,932 --> 02:04:02,015
Lamberto, 99 votes.

1293
02:04:02,143 --> 02:04:04,259
[SPEAKING ITALIAN]

1294
02:04:07,523 --> 02:04:12,814
[IN LATIN] Do you accept
your election as supreme pontiff?

1295
02:04:13,446 --> 02:04:19,192
[IN ITALIAN] Oh God, shed light on the
decision they have taken on my behalf.

1296
02:04:20,119 --> 02:04:21,780
[IN LATIN] I accept.

1297
02:04:21,955 --> 02:04:24,617
[IN LATIN] By what name
do you wish to be called?

1298
02:04:24,874 --> 02:04:27,866
[IN LATIN] John Paul the First.

1299
02:04:36,678 --> 02:04:39,340
[BELL TOLLING]

1300
02:04:51,150 --> 02:04:53,391
[JOHN PAUL I SPEAKING ITALIAN OVER P.A. ]

1301
02:04:57,573 --> 02:05:02,409
I will do things "right away,"
rather than in "a little while…"

1302
02:05:04,539 --> 02:05:07,041
REPORTER: <i>Frederick
Keinszig, known as "God's Banker,"</i>

1303
02:05:07,125 --> 02:05:09,867
<i>has been reported missing.</i>

1304
02:05:09,961 --> 02:05:16,708
<i>He was last seen leaving the Rome
offices of Vatican owned Immobiliare.</i>

1305
02:05:17,552 --> 02:05:21,011
<i>Also missing was a large sum
of money and several documents.</i>

1306
02:05:22,515 --> 02:05:24,552
Keinszig, you fool.

1307
02:05:24,642 --> 02:05:26,098
[TELEPHONE RINGING]

1308
02:05:28,104 --> 02:05:30,689
REPORTER [CONTINUES]: <i>His
absence casts further suspicion</i>

1309
02:05:30,773 --> 02:05:33,014
<i>on the dealings of the Vatican Bank.</i>

1310
02:05:33,109 --> 02:05:35,817
<i>For several years, the
bank and its companies</i>

1311
02:05:35,903 --> 02:05:40,147
<i>have been the object of allegations
of disreputable business practices.</i>

1312
02:05:41,367 --> 02:05:45,486
Lucchesi, will you
please try to understand?

1313
02:05:46,956 --> 02:05:51,200
I have phoned him.
I have waited here by the phone.

1314
02:05:53,838 --> 02:05:57,376
<i>You would do well to
remember, Mr. Lucchesi,</i>

1315
02:05:58,217 --> 02:06:04,884
that this Pope has very
different ideas from the last one.

1316
02:06:10,563 --> 02:06:12,349
[BLESSING IN LATIN]

1317
02:06:13,357 --> 02:06:14,392
[INAUDIBLE]

1318
02:06:27,121 --> 02:06:29,158
[WHISPERING] Goodbye, my old friend.

1319
02:06:31,876 --> 02:06:34,584
You could have lived a little longer.

1320
02:06:35,505 --> 02:06:37,997
[STAMMERING] I could
be closer to my dream.

1321
02:06:44,347 --> 02:06:46,884
You were so loved, Don Tommasino.

1322
02:06:51,729 --> 02:06:55,438
Why was I so feared, and you so loved?

1323
02:06:56,651 --> 02:06:58,267
What was it?

1324
02:06:59,445 --> 02:07:01,652
I was no less honorable.

1325
02:07:03,783 --> 02:07:05,615
I wanted to do good.

1326
02:07:09,747 --> 02:07:12,660
What betrayed me? My mind? My heart?

1327
02:07:15,753 --> 02:07:18,165
Why do I condemn myself so?

1328
02:07:24,762 --> 02:07:26,469
I swear,

1329
02:07:26,931 --> 02:07:29,172
on the lives of my children…

1330
02:07:33,729 --> 02:07:36,391
Give me a chance to redeem myself…

1331
02:07:40,361 --> 02:07:43,979
And I will sin no more.

1332
02:07:56,586 --> 02:07:57,917
[DOOR OPENING]

1333
02:08:08,222 --> 02:08:12,136
You look pale. Bad news?
Tell me right away.

1334
02:08:14,270 --> 02:08:16,728
It's not just a bad banking deal.

1335
02:08:17,773 --> 02:08:19,855
These guys are butchers.

1336
02:08:21,068 --> 02:08:23,730
-What guys?
-Lucchesi.

1337
02:08:25,573 --> 02:08:29,487
He controls all of them:
Altobello, the Archbishop

1338
02:08:31,287 --> 02:08:33,949
others higher up, P2 maybe.

1339
02:08:34,040 --> 02:08:37,078
Secret unknown. They're running things.

1340
02:08:40,880 --> 02:08:45,625
-I'm in their way.
-He's hired an assassin to kill you.

1341
02:08:46,260 --> 02:08:48,877
A Sicilian. I don't know his name.

1342
02:08:49,305 --> 02:08:50,966
[GRUNTS]

1343
02:08:51,057 --> 02:08:53,219
But they say he never fails.

1344
02:08:54,477 --> 02:08:56,593
Then no one is safe.

1345
02:08:59,440 --> 02:09:01,807
Even the new Pope is in danger.

1346
02:09:02,902 --> 02:09:05,985
We still have time. We can prevent this.

1347
02:09:11,410 --> 02:09:13,742
I tried, Vincent.

1348
02:09:15,915 --> 02:09:17,405
I tried

1349
02:09:18,751 --> 02:09:23,166
to keep everything from coming to this.
But it's not possible.

1350
02:09:24,715 --> 02:09:26,456
Not in this world.

1351
02:09:28,094 --> 02:09:29,801
Give me the order.

1352
02:09:33,683 --> 02:09:36,015
You won't be able to go back.

1353
02:09:37,061 --> 02:09:39,143
-You'll be like me.
-Good.

1354
02:09:40,940 --> 02:09:42,931
All my life I wanted out.

1355
02:09:43,651 --> 02:09:45,688
I wanted the family out.

1356
02:09:47,822 --> 02:09:49,654
I don't want out.

1357
02:09:50,116 --> 02:09:52,904
I want the power to preserve the family.

1358
02:09:57,623 --> 02:09:59,830
I'm asking for the order.

1359
02:10:20,813 --> 02:10:22,429
It's done.

1360
02:10:23,899 --> 02:10:26,186
Because I can't do it anymore.

1361
02:10:30,489 --> 02:10:34,073
Well, it doesn't matter.
Vincent knows what to do.

1362
02:10:34,160 --> 02:10:39,121
Come on outside.
Take a rest and don't think about it.

1363
02:10:39,498 --> 02:10:42,411
-All I do is think about it.
-I'm your son.

1364
02:10:43,586 --> 02:10:45,702
Command me in all things.

1365
02:10:48,049 --> 02:10:49,960
Give up my daughter.

1366
02:10:53,012 --> 02:10:55,174
That's the price you pay,

1367
02:10:56,307 --> 02:10:58,469
for the life you choose.

1368
02:11:24,668 --> 02:11:26,204
Nephew…

1369
02:11:28,672 --> 02:11:30,709
From this moment on

1370
02:11:32,134 --> 02:11:34,626
call yourself Vincent Corleone.

1371
02:11:39,433 --> 02:11:40,673
Sit.

1372
02:11:55,866 --> 02:11:57,482
Don Vincenzo…

1373
02:12:03,499 --> 02:12:05,206
Don Corleone…

1374
02:12:08,712 --> 02:12:10,828
Don Vincenzo Corleone…

1375
02:12:57,845 --> 02:12:59,711
[INDISTINCT CHATTERING]

1376
02:13:31,754 --> 02:13:34,712
[CHATTERING IN ITALIAN]

1377
02:13:44,600 --> 02:13:46,932
<i>E tu, Vincenzo…</i>

1378
02:13:47,061 --> 02:13:51,680
I know how you feel about
Michael, but you can't save him.

1379
02:13:52,608 --> 02:13:53,939
He's lost.

1380
02:13:55,611 --> 02:13:57,522
[WHISPERING] Think of yourself.

1381
02:13:58,447 --> 02:14:01,235
What's your answer, Vincent?

1382
02:14:02,743 --> 02:14:04,450
Enjoy the opera.

1383
02:14:06,580 --> 02:14:08,617
It's all taken care of.

1384
02:14:14,213 --> 02:14:16,955
Check the bar. I'll check the top floor.

1385
02:14:20,803 --> 02:14:25,218
"Here's hoping Tony sings better at
the Teatro Massimo than in the shower.

1386
02:14:25,307 --> 02:14:27,548
Love, Douglas."

1387
02:14:27,643 --> 02:14:31,056
-My darling Constanza!
-Don Altobello.

1388
02:14:31,981 --> 02:14:34,973
-This is a great occasion.
-Come, sit down.

1389
02:14:39,655 --> 02:14:44,149
Happy birthday.
You're 80, but don't look more than 60.

1390
02:14:44,243 --> 02:14:46,655
You're the only one who remembered.

1391
02:14:46,787 --> 02:14:48,494
We've just got the word.

1392
02:14:48,581 --> 02:14:51,994
The Pope has ratified the
Immobiliare deal. We've won.

1393
02:14:52,084 --> 02:14:53,745
Congratulations.

1394
02:14:56,589 --> 02:14:58,830
Strange how things work.

1395
02:14:58,966 --> 02:15:03,005
The Pope is doing what you said he'd do.
He's cleaning house.

1396
02:15:04,096 --> 02:15:07,839
He should be careful.
It's dangerous to be an honest man.

1397
02:15:08,809 --> 02:15:11,471
[CHATTERING IN ITALIAN]

1398
02:15:14,148 --> 02:15:17,186
[WHISPERING] I want to put
more muscle backstage with Tony.

1399
02:15:29,288 --> 02:15:32,531
On your birthday you used
to shower me with treats.

1400
02:15:32,666 --> 02:15:34,498
Tootsie Rolls!

1401
02:15:35,377 --> 02:15:40,838
The nuns who made this cannoli took
a vow of silence. They're the very finest.

1402
02:15:44,678 --> 02:15:47,386
-Hey.
-Hey, cous.

1403
02:15:49,475 --> 02:15:52,217
Hi. Where's your leather?

1404
02:15:56,398 --> 02:15:57,888
[WHISPERING] Stop it.

1405
02:16:03,906 --> 02:16:07,069
You're so thin. You eat it.

1406
02:16:23,759 --> 02:16:25,090
<i>È buono.</i>

1407
02:16:25,594 --> 02:16:27,926
<i>Grazie!</i>

1408
02:16:30,891 --> 02:16:35,180
It's over. There are things I
have to do that you can't be part of.

1409
02:16:35,270 --> 02:16:38,183
It's not your father's
decision, it's mine.

1410
02:16:40,109 --> 02:16:42,191
Don't hate your father.

1411
02:16:44,446 --> 02:16:48,280
There are things I'll be part
of that you can't be around.

1412
02:16:50,035 --> 02:16:52,777
After tonight, you won't see me anymore.

1413
02:16:57,126 --> 02:17:00,790
You've got to understand, Mary.
You've got to understand.

1414
02:17:01,797 --> 02:17:03,458
I'll always love you.

1415
02:17:16,645 --> 02:17:18,477
Love somebody else.

1416
02:17:27,823 --> 02:17:29,279
[MARY SOBBING]

1417
02:17:41,170 --> 02:17:43,081
[ALL TOASTING ANTHONY]

1418
02:17:46,592 --> 02:17:48,003
[AUDIENCE APPLAUDING]

1419
02:17:48,135 --> 02:17:50,342
[CHATTERING IN ITALIAN]

1420
02:18:03,025 --> 02:18:04,811
[MUSIC PLAYING]

1421
02:18:11,700 --> 02:18:14,112
[ANTHONY SINGING ITALIAN OPERA]

1422
02:18:15,370 --> 02:18:16,860
[INAUDIBLE]

1423
02:19:01,708 --> 02:19:03,494
[CHATTERING IN ITALIAN]

1424
02:19:29,611 --> 02:19:31,272
[WHISTLE BLOWING]

1425
02:19:42,791 --> 02:19:44,873
[DRAMATIC MUSIC PLAYING]

1426
02:20:03,979 --> 02:20:05,936
[SINGING]

1427
02:20:59,701 --> 02:21:01,035
VINCENT: They won't try anything.

1428
02:21:01,119 --> 02:21:03,611
BODYGUARD: Everything's fine.
It's all clear.

1429
02:21:03,705 --> 02:21:06,538
I've already sent Al Neri to the Vatican.

1430
02:21:19,054 --> 02:21:21,546
[IN ITALIAN] Mr. Lucchesi's house?

1431
02:21:21,682 --> 02:21:22,717
[IN ITALIAN] Yes.

1432
02:21:23,183 --> 02:21:27,393
I bring a message from Michael Corleone.

1433
02:21:28,814 --> 02:21:30,179
Let him in.

1434
02:21:31,233 --> 02:21:32,644
[DOOR BUZZING]

1435
02:21:55,215 --> 02:21:57,172
[SPEAKING ITALIAN]

1436
02:22:02,597 --> 02:22:04,213
[GRUNTS]

1437
02:22:29,958 --> 02:22:32,120
[AUDIENCE APPLAUDING FIERCELY]

1438
02:22:32,252 --> 02:22:33,959
[PEOPLE CHEERING]

1439
02:22:38,091 --> 02:22:40,423
[AUDIENCE APPLAUDING]

1440
